  "slug": "millionaires-shortbread",
  "title": "Millionaire's shortbread",
  "subtitle": "Shortbread base, caramel layer, chocolate top",
  "excerpt": "The three-layer slice: a shortbread base baked golden, a thick caramel of butter and condensed milk poured over and set, and a dark chocolate top scored into squares. Forty pieces from one 20 cm square tin.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "F. Marian McNeill, The Scots Kitchen (1929), records millionaire's shortbread (originally 'caramel shortbread') as a Scottish tea-table standard. Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136, includes the caramel-with-condensed-milk method in the sweets chapter. The use of sweetened condensed milk in caramel-making as a household standard is documented in USDA dairy bulletins of the 1920s (public domain).",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Millionaire's shortbread is three layers built one on top of the other in the same tin: a baked shortbread base, a poured caramel that sets firm, and a chocolate top scored before cutting. Patience between layers is the key. The shortbread must cool completely before the caramel goes on, the caramel must set firm before the chocolate, and the chocolate must be scored while just-soft then fully set before portioning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Worth making a day ahead. The caramel firms up overnight and the cut edges stay clean rather than tearing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "infoPanel",
        "attrs": {
          "body": "Caramel gets very hot. If it touches skin, run cold water over it and seek medical care if needed.",
          "tone": "warning",
          "title": "Caramel is hot"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What you need",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
